OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F382A1778529954
OL,3,CCarer guilty of using housebound
OL,4,Cpensioner's bank cards for lavish gifts
OL,6,FA Jersey carer stole around #7,000
OL,7,Ffrom a vulnerable pensioner she was
OL,8,Ftrusted to look after.
OL,10,FSandra Natalie Jardim De Sousa, 43,
OL,11,Fused the 80-year-old housebound
OL,12,Fwoman's bank cards for dozens of cash
OL,13,Fwithdrawals and personal purchases
OL,14,Fwhile working for Aurum Home Care.
OL,16,FIt afforded her lavish gifts such as
OL,17,FApple AirPods and an Apple Watch,
OL,18,Falongside cosmetics, clothing, a
OL,19,Fjuicer, a vacuum cleaner and other
OL,20,Fhousehold items bought from island
OL,21,Fshops.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G1/9
OL,2,W+.!/*%/*%/*%/*%+,"-$ /(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BCh Is News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,383,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38202
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F382A1778529954
OL,3,CCarer guilty of using housebound
OL,4,Cpensioner's bank cards for lavish gifts
OL,6,FDe Sousa pleaded innocence, but a jury
OL,7,Fconvicted her of all 12 offences after
OL,8,Fa trial and around five hours of
OL,9,Fdeliberation at Jersey's Royal Court.
OL,11,FShe was found guilty of four counts of
OL,12,Flarceny and eight of obtaining goods
OL,13,Funder false pretences.
OL,15,FThe offences started within eight
OL,16,Fmonths of De Sousa joining the care
OL,17,Fagency and only stopped after the
OL,18,Fpensioner's family became concerned
OL,19,Fabout suspicious withdrawals and
OL,20,Fspending on her bank accounts.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G2/9
OL,2,W+.!/*%/*%/*%/*%+,"-$ /(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BCh Is News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,383,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38203
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F382A1778529954
OL,3,CCarer guilty of using housebound
OL,4,Cpensioner's bank cards for lavish gifts
OL,6,FBetween November 2024 and March 2025,
OL,7,Fthe court heard how the vulnerable
OL,8,Fwoman's money was used for a wide
OL,9,Frange of purchases.
OL,11,FOn Christmas Eve, it paid for hundreds
OL,12,Fof pounds worth of shopping while De
OL,13,FSousa reportedly had just #17.50 in
OL,14,Fone of her own bank accounts.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G3/9
OL,2,W+.!/*%/*%/*%/*%+,"-$ /(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BCh Is News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,383,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38204
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F382A1778529954
OL,3,CCarer guilty of using housebound
OL,4,Cpensioner's bank cards for lavish gifts
OL,6,FThe 80-year-old victim, who had
OL,7,Frecently undergone major surgery and
OL,8,Fneeded extra support at home, told the
OL,9,Fcourt she felt "sick" after
OL,10,Fdiscovering what had happened and said
OL,11,Fshe had lost trust in the carers
OL,12,Fcoming into her home.
OL,14,FDuring the trial, De Sousa denied
OL,15,Facting dishonestly and claimed some
OL,16,Fpurchases were accidental, telling
OL,17,Fjurors she had mistakenly used the
OL,18,Fwoman's card while stressed and
OL,19,Frushing between care visits.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G4/9
OL,2,W+.!/*%/*%/*%/*%+,"-$ /(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BCh Is News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,383,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38205
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F382A1778529954
OL,3,CCarer guilty of using housebound
OL,4,Cpensioner's bank cards for lavish gifts
OL,6,FShe also insisted that cash
OL,7,Fwithdrawals had been authorised and
OL,8,Fhanded back to the woman.
OL,10,FHowever, prosecutors argued the
OL,11,Fpattern of spending and repeated
OL,12,Finstances of taking out money showed
OL,13,FDe Sousa had been using the
OL,14,Fpensioner's money for her own benefit.
OL,16,FFollowing the guilty verdict, the
OL,17,Fjudge described the offences as "an
OL,18,Fabuse of trust".
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G5/9
OL,2,W+.!/*%/*%/*%/*%+,"-$ /(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BCh Is News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,383,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38206
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F382A1778529954
OL,3,CCarer guilty of using housebound
OL,4,Cpensioner's bank cards for lavish gifts
OL,6,FDe Sousa was granted conditional bail
OL,7,Ffor 48 hours to allow arrangements to
OL,8,Fbe made for her children before she is
OL,9,Fremanded into custody.
OL,11,FShe will be sentenced on Wednesday 24
OL,12,FJune.
OL,14,FFollowing the verdict, Aurum Home
OL,15,FCare, which employed De Sousa, says:
OL,16,F"Our thoughts remain with the
OL,17,Fvulnerable lady at the centre of this
OL,18,Fcase and her loved ones.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G6/9
OL,2,W+.!/*%/*%/*%/*%+,"-$ /(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BCh Is News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,383,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38207
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F382A1778529954
OL,3,CCarer guilty of using housebound
OL,4,Cpensioner's bank cards for lavish gifts
OL,6,F"What has happened is deeply
OL,7,Fupsetting, and as a care organisation,
OL,8,Fit has affected all of us emotionally.
OL,10,F"We would like to reassure everyone
OL,11,Fthat Aurum Home Care have never been
OL,12,Funder investigation and at no point
OL,13,Fhave we been accused of wrongdoing in
OL,14,Frelation to this matter."
OL,16,FDetective Constable Jess Brown from
OL,17,Fthe States of Jersey Police adds: "The
OL,18,Fdefendant abused a clear position of
OL,19,Ftrust, taking money from the victim
OL,20,Ffor personal gain.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G7/9
OL,2,W+.!/*%/*%/*%/*%+,"-$ /(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BCh Is News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,383,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38208
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F382A1778529954
OL,3,CCarer guilty of using housebound
OL,4,Cpensioner's bank cards for lavish gifts
OL,6,F"This case highlights the seriousness
OL,7,Fof financial abuse and the harm it
OL,8,Fcauses to vulnerable people.
OL,10,F"Protecting those at risk remains a
OL,11,Fpriority, and we will always act where
OL,12,Fthat trust is broken."
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G8/9
